		<a name="38723"></a>
		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/11/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 11:42:20</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=5318"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=5318')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=38723&amp;TOPIC_ID=4886&amp;FORUM_ID=3&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=Necromancer+Game+Guides&amp;Topic_Title=Four+blues+needed+to+hit+55&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Furbys in OOT got a level bump a few patches ago (they are considered Giants) and many are still dark blue at 55.  Your pet can tank them solo, and you can chain pull if you shadowbond your pet.</P><P>Better way : get two or three friends 49+, everybody makes a good Pet49 and /pet guard here's them in a line, take turns chain pulling furbys into the meatgrinder of pets.  No casting, no healing, no medding, and as you can handle a multipull of up to 4 at once after you get the hang of it, the xp can be pretty good.  You should be able to keep the island clean.</P><P>Even better way, get three friends with Pet49 and add a bard to pull for you, bards run FAST and have tracking.  The XP bonus almost offsets his share of the XP and you will actually kill more Furbys with him chainpulling.</P><P>Glonoin</P><P>PS - Furby is Seafury Cyclops on the island after the AC island on the right side (third island you see off the right side when coming in from Freeport)</P><P>PPS - bind in East Freeport.  Bring a LOT of food and drink and bone chips.  Trust me on both of those.</P><P>Using your dead bodies to create a better tomorrow..<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

